en_184920_0	The Government Surveyors' Union says they would launch an indefinite strike from 08th of March against a move by the government to handover surveying of lands in Sri Lanka to an American firm.
en_184920_1	The Union's President Duminda Undugoda said they have already launched an internal trade union action to show their protest against the planned move.
en_184920_2	Meanwhile, a strike action launched by the university non-academic staff on 28th of last month citing several demands is continuing.
en_184920_3	A trade union representative said that the authorities are yet to respond to their demands.
en_184920_4	Meanwhile, the Public Health Inspectors in Puttalam are also planning to stage a strike seeking solutions for issues relating to their transfers and service centres.
